summary: SummaryNARS' iconic Blush, now reimagined in an upgraded formula that lasts for up to 16 hours, featuring true-color payoff with a comfortable, weightless feel.
details: DetailsFeaturesLasts for up to 16 hours with a comfortable, weightless feelPure Pigment Blend delivers high-impact, true-color payoffIrresistibly silky, blendable formula glides on smoothly and evenlyBlurs imperfectionsComfortable, weightless feelCan't get enough? This Blush compact is refillable in select shades, compatible with NARS Blush RefillKey IngredientsPure Pigment Blend, an innovative combination of four versatile pigments are combined for the ultimate results:Naturally-derived pigments deliver true-color payoffMineral-based pigments ensure a high-impact effectPearlescent pigments help blur the look of imperfectionsSuperfine, micronized pigments provide an irresistibly silky, blendable applicationFormulated WithoutTalc, Parabens, Phthalates, Mineral Oil, SulfatesItem 2621261How To UseThe strongest color payoff will be at the first point of brush contact to skin. Start application where the strongest color impact is desired.For a natural rush of color, gently buff color onto skin using sweeping circular motions with NARS #16 Blush Brush for more color payoff, or the NARS Yachiyo Brush for softer color payoff (brushes sold separately).For a seamless pop of color, layer two shades of Blush. Start with a base color in a shade that gives a subtle color to the cheeks. Layer a brighter shade in a similar tone on the apples of the cheek, then blend edges to diffuse into base color.For a touch-up or additional coverage, use a stippling motion when applying Blush to press color onto skin without disrupting coverage already created.Can't get enough? This Blush compact is refillable in select shades, compatible with NARS Blush Refill.IngredientsSynthetic Fluorphlogopite, Mica, Zinc Stearate, Magnesium Myristate, Octyldodecyl Stearoyl Stearate, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Tin Oxide, 1,2-Hexanediol, Caprylyl Glycol, Aluminum Hydroxide, Kaolin, Barium Sulfate, [+/-(May Contain/Peut Contenir): Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410), Red 30 (CI 73360), Red 33 Lake (CI 17200), Red 7 (CI 15850), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891)].Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: NARS blush reigns supreme
reviews.comments: Flawless formula, both matte and glowy shades. Velvety, effortlessly blendable, and perfect for any skin type

reviews.headline: Formula Change?
reviews.comments: Color, while complementary to my skin tone, is not as vibrant or long lasting as my other NARS. It also seems to have a new ingredient that irritates my skin. With how expensive NARS is, likely won't purchase again.

reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: It goes on nicely, and blends in nicely.  More on the red side rather than the softer pink or peach side.

reviews.headline: I will continue purchasing again and again!
reviews.comments: I received this blush as a gift some time ago and I really liked the quality but the shade was not my favorite so I didn't use it too often. Recently I was looking for a new go-to blush and decided to purchase this brand but a different shade than what I had and really loved it! It has great pigment and blends in perfectly with my makeup! It has become my favorite blush and will continue purchasing in the future!

reviews.headline: Dolce Vita!  Wow!
reviews.comments: I bought this blush in Dolce Vita. I wish in store lighting was better for choosing colors, but I lucked out. I have light skin. In summer, I'm slightly tanner. This color blush is gorgeous and looks very natural. BUT it is VERY pigmented.  I tap off my fluffy blush brush before applying it to my skin. I apply it to my cheek bones, temples and forehead nearer the hairline. I think it can also help to use translucent powder over liquid foundation before applying this blush so it doesn't over apply to some areas.  This is a blush that can look like true flushed or slightly sun burned skin. If you are light skinned, don't be afraid of this rich color.

reviews.headline: Not so good any more.
reviews.comments: Im pretty sure the formula is changed.  This blush is too expensive to not give any payoff on the brush or on your cheeks.

reviews.headline: Holy grail
reviews.comments: So flattering and last all day

reviews.headline: Formula change, blush is hard as ROCK
reviews.comments: I wish I read all the bad reviews about the formula change. I repurchased this because its my go to blush. And the new formula is absolutely horrible, it doesn't even come on to the brush. Im outside of the return policy so now Im stuck with this horrible product.

reviews.headline: love this blush
reviews.comments: applys nicely on top of creme blushes and it gives some glow

reviews.headline: New formula is not good
reviews.comments: Like someone else posted, my first review did not show upâ€¦ I have used a couple different shades for 15+ years. This new formula has zero color payoff. Would not purchase again.

reviews.headline: Beautiful
reviews.comments: This is my first Nars product and blush and I love the color! Its smooth and a little goes far luckily!

reviews.headline: I do buy this product again and again
reviews.comments: Great quality, nice coverage . Long lasting

reviews.headline: Not a fan of the new formula. Way less pigmented.
reviews.comments: I've been using the original NARS orgasm color for years, and it's always been my favorite. Finally ran out of my stockpile and had to buy one of these new formula ones. It's nice they're talc-free but the color is much lighter, less pigmented, and the actual formula has changed and feels more powdery to me. Not a fan, very sad, hope they can improve on this new formula ASAP.

reviews.headline: I would buy this again
reviews.comments: I love the color.  Has the perfect sheen to as well.  It's the perfect shade of peachy pink.  It goes on smooth.  Last's a long time.  Will buy it again.

reviews.headline: Dry and no color payoff
reviews.comments: Im so dissatisfied with the new formulation. Not even close to the color payoff the OG blush had.

reviews.headline: Believe the poor reviews
reviews.comments: Nars use to carry my all time favorite blushes, Orgasm and Sin. Now they carry my least favorite blushes. Sin has been discontinued and havent found a replacement yet. The reformulation has no pigment. Its really bad. Orgasm may as well of been discontinued. Its not like the original. Doesnt show up. And im very fair. I can't believe someone approved this. Especially with such a cult classic shade. Idk whats up with Nars lately. Possible dupes are YSL-Make Me Blush, shade 93 for Orgasm and LH Cosmetics- Duo Dimension, shade Area for Sin. But hey, at least the new packaging is nice. You can pop the pans out. I just wouldnt want to anymore.

reviews.headline: Color Options
reviews.comments: I was trying to buy the original shade of Nars Orgasm blush and ended up with one that is much lighter.  I wish they would have tagged the OG.

reviews.headline: A Classic for a Reason
reviews.comments: I've been using this blush for years and it truly is the best!

reviews.headline: Pleasantly surprised
reviews.comments: I have been using the Orgasm shade for several years. I tried the shade #237 and I was pleasantly surprised that it was a bit darker than my fave but it looked really nice and seems to last all day.

reviews.headline: Nars blush
reviews.comments: Really nice blush. Good color. Lasts all day

faceoff_positive.comments:
NARS has always been synonymous with sophistication and quality, and their Talc-Free Powder Blush in the shade Orgasm Edge â€“ 778 is no exception. As a devoted makeup enthusiast, I'm always on the lookout for products that deliver both style and substance, and this blush certainly hits the mark.

First and foremost, let's talk about the color. Orgasm Edge â€“ 778 is a stunning matte peachy pink that effortlessly complements a variety of skin tones. It adds a subtle flush of warmth to the cheeks, giving off a radiant, lit-from-within glow that instantly brightens up the complexion. Whether you're going for a natural daytime look or a more glam evening vibe, this shade is incredibly versatile and can be easily built up for intensity or applied sheer for a more understated effect.

What sets this blush apart is not just its gorgeous hue, but also its talc-free formula. As someone with sensitive skin, I greatly appreciate that NARS has formulated this product without talc, ensuring that it's gentle and non-irritating. Instead, it's enriched with skin-loving ingredients that not only deliver beautiful color payoff but also nourish and care for the skin.

In terms of texture, the powder is finely milled and silky-smooth, gliding effortlessly onto the skin without any patchiness or cakiness. It blends like a dream, seamlessly melding with the skin for a natural-looking finish that lasts throughout the day. Whether you're applying it with a fluffy brush for a diffused effect or with a denser brush for more precision, the result is always flawless.

Overall, I can't recommend the NARS Talc-Free Powder Blush in Orgasm Edge â€“ 778 highly enough. With its stunning color, talc-free formula, and impeccable quality, it's become a staple in my makeup collection. Whether you're a makeup aficionado or a beauty beginner, this blush is sure to become your new go-to for achieving a radiant, healthy-looking complexion.

Review:

NARS Talc-Free Powder Blush in the shade Orgasm Edge â€“ 778 is a versatile and high-quality product that delivers a beautiful flush of color to the cheeks. As someone who appreciates makeup that is both effective and gentle on the skin, I was excited to try this blush, and it did not disappoint.

One of the great things about this product is its ease of use. The compact packaging makes it perfect for on-the-go touch-ups, and the included mirror is a convenient addition for quick application. To use the blush, simply swirl a blush brush into the product, tap off any excess, and then gently apply to the apples of the cheeks, blending upwards towards the temples for a natural-looking flush.

The color Orgasm Edge â€“ 778 is a gorgeous matte peachy pink that adds a subtle warmth to the complexion. It's incredibly flattering on a wide range of skin tones and can be easily built up for more intensity or applied sheer for a softer effect. Plus, the talc-free formula ensures that it's gentle and non-irritating, making it suitable for even the most sensitive skin types.

In terms of performance, this blush truly shines. The powder is finely milled and blends seamlessly into the skin, leaving behind a smooth, natural finish that lasts throughout the day. It's also highly pigmented, so a little goes a long way, meaning that the compact will last for quite some time.

However, one thing to note is that because of its intense pigmentation, it's important to use a light hand when applying this blush to avoid overdoing it. Additionally, while the compact packaging is convenient for travel, it can be a bit bulky for everyday use, especially if you prefer to carry minimal makeup with you.

Overall, NARS Talc-Free Powder Blush in Orgasm Edge â€“ 778 is a fantastic product that delivers beautiful color payoff in a gentle, talc-free formula. Its ease of use, flattering shade, and long-lasting performance make it a standout addition to any makeup collection, despite minor drawbacks such as the potential for over-application and slightly bulky packaging.
faceoff_positive.headline: I would buy this product again and again

faceoff_negative.comments:
NARS Blush in Orgasm Rush is a product that certainly creates a buzz, but its performance may leave some users feeling lukewarm. While it boasts the same beloved formula as the original Orgasm blush, the "Rush" variation tends to lean more towards a brown hue rather than the expected red tones.

For those who prefer a warmer, more bronzed look, the shift towards brown may be a welcome change. However, for fans of the iconic pinky-red flush that Orgasm is famous for, this alteration may come as a disappointment. The color payoff can vary depending on skin tone, with some finding it too subtle and others appreciating its understated, natural finish.

Despite its deviation from the classic Orgasm shade, NARS Blush in Orgasm Rush still delivers on quality. The finely milled powder blends effortlessly onto the skin, providing a soft, buildable flush that lasts throughout the day. Plus, its universally flattering shimmer adds a luminous touch to the complexion, enhancing the overall look.
faceoff_negative.headline: It's more brown than red
